article.headline: Seton Hall 72, DePaul 49
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. -- Eugene Harvey scored 19 points and Robert Mitchell added 16 points and nine rebounds as Seton Hall defeated DePaul 72-49 on Tuesday night. Jeremy Hazell scored 13 points for Seton Hall (14-9, 5-6 Big East), which never trailed in the game. The Pirates have won five straight. Jordan Theodore added 11 points for Seton Hall, which went on an 8-0 run to boost the score at halftime to 40-24. DePaul (8-17, 0-12) was never close after the break. Seton Hall held DePaul to 30 percent shooting in the second half on 7-23 shooting from the field. The Blue Demons, who are winless in the Big East, were 2-for-9 from 3-point range. Dar Tucker finished with 19 points and Mac Koshwal added 11 points and 16 rebounds for DePaul.
